
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to concatenate strings to dynamically construct a SQL "CREATE TABLE" statement. It uses the [strings.concat] slot to combine static strings with values retrieved from arguments, specifically [tableName], [pkName], and [type], to form the complete SQL command. The snippet showcases the use of [get-value] to fetch argument values and integrate them into the concatenated string.
strings.concat
   .:"create table "
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/tableName
   .:(
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/pkName
   .:" "
   get-value:x:@.type
